												<div class="description author withsidebar">
													<h6><a href="https://lithub.com/author/sunilamrith/">Sunil Amrith</a></h6>
													Sunil Amrith is the Renu and Anand Dhawan Professor of History at Yale University and professor at the Yale School of the Environment. He is the author of five books, most recently <em>The Burning Earth</em>, and recipient of multiple awards, including a MacArthur "genius" fellowship, a fellowship at the British Academy, and the 2024 Fukuoka Prize. He grew up in Singapore and lives in Connecticut.																									</div>
